text: <@UCRK0QBPZ> - <@U3PKJ8EQL> just launched x2 new lessons (HubL and HubDB)... Now he's hustling on the last 2 lessons for an early Q1 launch. After all the lessons are live, he's then thinking through how to do a (scalable) way to test/practicum for a certification. Once we have a good plan for that, we'll launch it as an official "Certification" I'd ballpark end Q1/early Q2.
We want to set a really high bar for someone to become certified. it will be hard. (the previous "design" cert was super easy that even marketers could pass it :see_no_evil:)

this is great to get started... also make sure to check out the Discovery Kit... which was specifically built for onboarding new developers.

<https://designers.HubSpot.com/discoverykit>

Make sure to check out all the linked resources... there is a lot of great stuff in there.
